    "size": 334651
  },
  "news": [
    {
      "title": "Stop held items clipping the bottom-right corner (anchor pulled up/in)",
      "date": "2026-06-24",
      "body": "Moved the viewmodel hand anchor up and slightly inward so torches and narrow items stay fully visible in the lower-right instead of being cut off by the screen edge."
    },
    {
      "title": "Match held-item pose to Beta reference (tilt, scale, corner anchor)",
      "date": "2026-06-24",
      "body": "Flipped the in-plane tilt the correct way, restored scale to 0.5, and anchored the handle in the bottom-right corner so the pickaxe reaches toward centre and the torch leans up-left, matching the Beta screenshots."
    },
    {
      "title": "Tune held-item pose toward Beta (smaller, lower-right, corrected tilt)",
      "date": "2026-06-24",
      "body": "Scaled the 3D held item down (0.62->0.42), pushed the hand anchor into the lower-right corner, and adjusted the in-plane tilt so tools/torches sit like Beta instead of looming large and central. The extrusion pipeline itself is unchanged."
    },
    {
      "title": "Extruded 3D held-item pipeline — items render as real models with depth",
      "date": "2026-06-24",
      "body": "Replaced the flat-quad held item with a HeldItemRenderer that extrudes each icon into a 3D mesh: per opaque texel a front+back face plus silhouette side faces, one texel thick, with baked per-face shade via a new item.vert/frag. Meshes cache per atlas layer, so every tool/stick/torch and any future item gets real depth automatically. Empty hand uses the same renderer's shaded box on the skin tile; held full blocks stay cubes. Added TextureAtlas.texelSolid."
    },
    {
      "title": "Beta-accurate first-person swing, single-sprite torches, breakable placed torches",
      "date": "2026-06-24",
      "body": "Rebuilt the viewmodel swing to match Minecraft Beta: translate to the hand first, then rotateY(45) and the swing rotations (f7 -20 Y, f8 -20 Z, f8 -80 X) so the item pivots at the hand and swings down-and-inward instead of sideways. One swing curve for mining/placing/attacking."
    },
    {
      "title": "True 3D first-person viewmodel + a rebuilt pause menu",
      "date": "2026-06-22",
      "body": "Replaced the 2D held-item with a real 3D viewmodel via CubeRenderer: anchor a local transform to inverse(camera.view()) so it renders in clean view space. Held blocks are textured cubes, tools/items angled sprites, empty hand a 3D arm on a new procedural skin tile. Depth cleared first so the world can't clip it; per-type swings rotate it in 3D; walk-bob translates it."
    },
    {
      "title": "First-person hand & held items with Beta-style swings, bigger inventory, cleaner pause/settings",
      "date": "2026-06-22",
      "body": "Added a screen-space first-person viewmodel: held item icon in the lower-right that replaces a procedurally-drawn arm when empty (never both). Swing animations - mining arc, quick place flick, dedicated sword swing - hooked off the mine/place inputs and looping while held. Walk bob eases with player speed."
    },
    {
      "title": "Credits & Multiplayer now live in the real menu scene, camera craning to the castle",
      "date": "2026-06-22",
      "body": "Dropped the separate campfire scene. Both pages stay on the live key-art (clouds/fog still moving) while a new push param on MenuBackground.render slowly cranes the framing toward the distant castle. Shared cinematic title-card: letterbox bars ease in, a soft scrim darkens only the left edge, and the names fade in as a left-aligned column with a big ember-gold hero. Minimal Return hint, no box. UI stays under 20% of the screen."
    }
  ],
